1. Customer looks for a green signal on parking display board to check the availability.
2. Parking automated system checks for the availability slot and assigns the ticket to the customer.
3. The ticket contains info such as vehicle number, date, time of arrival and available parking slot number.
4. PAS opens the welcome barrier and update the parking display board.
5. Customer parks the ticket at the assigned place.
6. Customer scans the ticket at the exit where PAS calculates the amount and generates the bill.
7. Customer makes the payment via cash or card.
8. PAS opens the exit barrier and update the parking display board.